ost the =E2=80=9922 mayoral race to Bass,
is apparently deciding whether he wants a rematch=E2=80=94or to try his han=
d at the governor=E2=80=99s mansion, which would put him squarely in the cr=
osshairs of Harris, who is ostensibly eyeing that seat. In Caruso, Kamala, =
and the Battle for L.A. ( https://puck.news/rick-caruso-political-ambitions=
-expand-beyond-los-angeles/?utm_campaign=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282=
%2F15%2F25%29&utm_content=3DThe+Backstory+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F15%2F25%29&u=
tm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42ab=
d12a ), Peter gracefully articulates the endless and intractable nuances of=
 the political situation. Caruso, of course, has
been portrayed as a Trumpian figure, but he also projects a kind of can-do =
aplomb that=E2=80=99s currently appealing in the Democratic diaspora of L.A=
=2E (As a lifelong New Yorker, I=E2=
=80=99m reminded of Giuliani=E2=80=99s app=
eal to citydwellers after the Koch=E2=80=93Dinkins era. That story, of cour=
se, took a weird twist.)

=C2=A0

Caruso also seems to define himself as a post-partisan
bullshit assassin=E2=80=94the kind of guy made for a new era when old polit=
ical fault lines seem outdated. You may not agree with his politics, but I =
have to admit I found his worldview at least a little refreshing=E2=80=94a =
positive development, as it were, amid a cavalcade of disturbing regression=
s. =E2=80=9CI think we=E2=80=99ve got to get out of the business of, if you=
 have an R behind your name or a D behind your name, you=E2=80=99re either =
right or you=E2=80=99re wrong, or you=E2=80=99re not allowed to talk to eac=
h other,=E2=80=9D Caruso told Peter.
=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s just such a foolish way to try to manage this country=
=2E Donald Trump is the president of th=
e United States, period. End of story.=
 And we need his help and we need federal dollars. And I was grateful that =
he was actually pushing the elected officials, Get this done. Now we need m=
ore of that. So of course I would work with Trump. I would have worked with=
 Joe Biden. That doesn=E2=80=99t matter, and it shouldn=E2=80=99t matter to=
 anybody.=E2=80=9D

=C2=A0

Indeed, more than anything else, this realignment is the story of our time=
=E2=80=94and it=E2=80=99s one with endless applications across our economy.=
 It=E2=80=99s also precisely what you should expect to read about in Puck.

=E2=80=8A

