 never <em>actually</em> push to sew up the loophole. Revealingly, the whol=
e scenario reminded Bill
of a conversation he=E2=80=99d had with Apollo C.E.O. <strong>Marc Rowan </=
strong>a couple years earlier. =E2=80=9CWhy do you think the carried intere=
st tax comes up every time there=E2=80=99s an election?=E2=80=9D Rowan aske=
d Bill, rhetorically, at the time. =E2=80=9CBecause the Dems know it=E2=80=
